1
00:00:04,740 --> 00:00:05,950
I'm so sorry.

2
00:00:06,620 --> 00:00:08,880
I've come down with a fever.

3
00:00:10,990 --> 00:00:11,990
Yes.

4
00:00:12,830 --> 00:00:14,440
I should be able to make it in tomorrow.

5
00:00:15,860 --> 00:00:16,860
Okay.

6
00:00:22,140 --> 00:00:23,140
*Sigh*

7
00:00:23,870 --> 00:00:25,920
I shouldn't have hung
around there after that.

8
00:00:26,310 --> 00:00:28,510
I should've just gone straight home.

9
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:33,636
Did you think that just because you called,

10
00:00:33,660 --> 00:00:35,310
I'd come running to you?

11
00:00:35,930 --> 00:00:38,070
What do you even know about me?

12
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:40,240
We've only slept together a few times.

13
00:00:41,330 --> 00:00:42,810
Let's not see each other for a while.

14
00:00:48,930 --> 00:00:51,190
How long is "for a while" supposed to be?

15
00:00:52,670 --> 00:00:54,070
Dammit!

16
00:00:59,350 --> 00:01:01,880
For a while.

17
00:01:03,280 --> 00:01:06,220
(Online Dictionary) Refers to a
short time, but not immediately.

18
00:01:07,530 --> 00:01:09,360
What am I even looking up?

19
00:01:17,710 --> 00:01:20,010
People are surprisingly fragile.

20
00:01:21,980 --> 00:01:24,870
Apparently, you can
die just from dehydration.

21
00:01:25,660 --> 00:01:29,090
If I collapse like this, I'm in trouble.

22
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:34,680
Even getting a glass
of water is a struggle.

23
00:01:37,290 --> 00:01:38,420
At a time like this,

24
00:01:38,890 --> 00:01:41,650
I don't have anyone I can just call.

25
00:01:48,260 --> 00:01:50,990
I can't reach out to anyone.

26
00:01:54,750 --> 00:01:55,750
Whatever.

27
00:01:55,940 --> 00:01:56,940
It doesn't matter.

28
00:01:57,550 --> 00:01:59,320
There's no point in trying so hard anymore.

29
00:01:59,980 --> 00:02:01,690
I have nothing left to lose.

30
00:02:04,530 --> 00:02:05,900
Ah...

31
00:02:06,530 --> 00:02:07,650
But still...

32
00:02:08,550 --> 00:02:09,990
If I could, I'd really like to...

33
00:02:10,950 --> 00:02:12,100
one last time...

34
00:02:14,210 --> 00:02:15,210
Kaji.

35
00:02:16,250 --> 00:02:17,250
Kaji.

36
00:02:19,450 --> 00:02:20,450
Are you okay?

37
00:02:22,380 --> 00:02:23,380
What are you doing here?

38
00:02:24,630 --> 00:02:26,030
Didn't you call me?

39
00:02:27,940 --> 00:02:29,280
Did I?

40
00:02:34,930 --> 00:02:36,070
You're burning up.

41
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:37,870
Here, drink something first.

42
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:51,250
Your mouth is so hot.

43
00:02:52,530 --> 00:02:53,530
I'll catch it.

44
00:02:55,030 --> 00:02:57,630
Yeah, you probably will.

45
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:00,220
But I can't help it.

46
00:03:01,270 --> 00:03:02,270
I'm sorry,

47
00:03:03,630 --> 00:03:05,970
but I want to give it to you.

48
00:03:21,330 --> 00:03:22,630
Can we just

49
00:03:23,850 --> 00:03:25,070
stay like this all day?

50
00:03:30,150 --> 00:03:31,150
This feels nice.

51
00:03:31,830 --> 00:03:32,830
Like this,

52
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:36,540
it feels like I don't have
to worry about anything.

53
00:03:47,090 --> 00:03:48,480
Touch me.

54
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:51,320
I'll comfort you too.

55
00:04:14,970 --> 00:04:15,970
Oh no...

56
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:18,740
I'm going to come.

57
00:04:21,196 --> 00:04:22,196
Kaji.

58
00:04:23,290 --> 00:04:24,410
Let's kiss.

59
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:33,670
It's like a dream.

60
00:04:41,820 --> 00:04:42,820
Kaji.

61
00:04:43,810 --> 00:04:45,950
Is this okay?

62
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:49,830
Fukami...

63
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:52,360
I told him we shouldn't
see each other for a while,

64
00:04:52,700 --> 00:04:54,560
but I didn't mean it.

65
00:04:56,460 --> 00:04:57,660
I really wanted

66
00:04:57,940 --> 00:04:59,210
to be kinder to him.

67
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:06,860
A dream?

68
00:05:15,270 --> 00:05:17,420
Just kill me now.

69
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,500
"Unexpectedly Naughty Fukami"

70
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:22,410
At times like this, I need to work.

71
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,750
Use work to forget all
these useless worries.

72
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,610
Sorry to worry you.

73
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:28,376
(Episode 5)
My fever's gone down a bit.

74
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:30,300
I'll work from home for now.

75
00:05:31,050 --> 00:05:32,050
Huh?

76
00:05:32,250 --> 00:05:33,679
If you don't rest,

77
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:35,520
HR will be all over me.

78
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:37,430
Just take the day off.

79
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:45,070
Being idle just makes things worse.

80
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:50,819
If I can't work,

81
00:05:50,820 --> 00:05:52,890
I might as well deal with this frustration.

82
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,060
Having dreams like that

83
00:05:55,470 --> 00:05:57,000
is just a sign of being unsatisfied.

84
00:06:06,150 --> 00:06:07,150
Is he

85
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:08,450
still mad?

86
00:06:09,930 --> 00:06:11,630
Wait, he never

87
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:14,000
asked if he was the only one anyway.

88
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,400
(40-pointer: Want to meet today?)

89
00:06:21,490 --> 00:06:23,230
He's got a decent face,

90
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:25,500
but he's a loud "40-point" guy.

91
00:06:32,490 --> 00:06:34,330
As long as I don't get
attached to one person,

92
00:06:34,850 --> 00:06:36,990
I won't have to feel this pathetic.

93
00:06:41,380 --> 00:06:43,480
Wait, do we really need all these files?

94
00:06:43,890 --> 00:06:44,790
Please.

95
00:06:44,791 --> 00:06:46,499
Kaji-kun still has a high fever.

96
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:47,920
Let him rest.

97
00:06:48,050 --> 00:06:49,560
Oh, fine.

98
00:06:49,850 --> 00:06:50,850
I get it.

99
00:06:51,730 --> 00:06:54,030
Get well soon, Kaji-san.

100
00:07:07,490 --> 00:07:08,830
Come on in.

101
00:07:09,210 --> 00:07:10,900
Have a seat on the sofa.

102
00:07:13,010 --> 00:07:15,470
I'm surprised you invited me over.

103
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,160
Want to shower first?

104
00:07:20,950 --> 00:07:22,570
You seem like a different person.

105
00:07:24,210 --> 00:07:26,740
Usually you're ready to kick
me out the second we're done.

106
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:29,960
Am I?

107
00:07:30,380 --> 00:07:31,380
Yeah.

108
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:34,280
But

109
00:07:34,570 --> 00:07:35,800
I didn't mind it that way.

110
00:07:38,830 --> 00:07:39,830
Actually...

111
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,340
Can I shower first?

112
00:07:41,830 --> 00:07:42,930
I'm all sweaty.

113
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:57,600
(Zero-point guy: I'm nearby. Are you home?)

114
00:07:57,640 --> 00:07:58,640
Zero points.

115
00:08:05,180 --> 00:08:06,380
What is this?

116
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:10,520
I used to think love

117
00:08:11,310 --> 00:08:14,400
was something I didn't need in my life.

118
00:08:18,340 --> 00:08:19,980
Even today,

119
00:08:22,450 --> 00:08:23,780
I just felt like

120
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:25,580
I wanted to do it.

121
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:33,470
It's so embarrassing.

122
00:08:34,070 --> 00:08:36,440
Acting all desperate
like some guy in a porn.

123
00:08:37,300 --> 00:08:38,720
I should be more composed.

124
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:40,850
Like, just kissing and stuff.

125
00:08:47,460 --> 00:08:48,900
Wait, right here?

126
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,060
When I'm with you,

127
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:54,950
I don't feel like myself anymore.

128
00:09:03,660 --> 00:09:05,150
- Never mind.
- Akihiro.

129
00:09:07,780 --> 00:09:08,980
You should at least know

130
00:09:09,690 --> 00:09:11,580
the name of the person
you're sleeping with.

131
00:09:16,220 --> 00:09:19,320
Why am I realizing this now of all times?

132
00:09:30,690 --> 00:09:31,790
That took a while.

133
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:34,200
Hey...

134
00:09:37,580 --> 00:09:38,580
Sorry.

135
00:09:44,630 --> 00:09:46,980
You really didn't have
to walk me to the station.

136
00:09:47,260 --> 00:09:48,420
At least let me do this much.

137
00:09:49,840 --> 00:09:51,080
I hope things work out for you.

138
00:09:52,430 --> 00:09:53,430
I'm sorry.

139
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:56,160
I told you, stop apologizing.

140
00:10:01,370 --> 00:10:02,370
Fukami.

141
00:10:07,080 --> 00:10:08,540
I was in the neighborhood

142
00:10:09,950 --> 00:10:11,590
and heard you were sick.

143
00:10:13,860 --> 00:10:15,020
Oh.

144
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:17,980
So you're the "Zero-point guy."

145
00:10:19,460 --> 00:10:21,450
I saw his contact list.

146
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:23,380
He actually rates every guy he knows.

147
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,500
I'm a 40.

148
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,290
And you're a zero.

149
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:29,150
Funny, right?

150
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:32,510
I can't believe I kept in
touch with a guy like this.

151
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:35,820
I'm an idiot for coming
running the moment you called.

152
00:10:38,210 --> 00:10:40,380
This guy looks down on everyone.

153
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:42,050
Me,

154
00:10:42,330 --> 00:10:43,330
and you too.

155
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:46,540
Rating people

156
00:10:48,050 --> 00:10:50,010
and tossing them aside
whenever he feels like it.

157
00:10:50,910 --> 00:10:52,370
Who does that?

158
00:10:56,690 --> 00:10:58,650
You're better off not
wasting your time with him.

159
00:11:02,065 --> 00:11:03,510
What is he talking about?

160
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:06,850
He's totally got the wrong idea.

161
00:11:10,250 --> 00:11:11,250
I don't want

162
00:11:11,540 --> 00:11:12,540
to keep lying to myself

163
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:15,260
in front of this man anymore.

164
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:19,400
I'm sorry.

165
00:11:26,580 --> 00:11:28,230
I know I'm terrible.

166
00:11:29,430 --> 00:11:30,520
About the "zero points"...

167
00:11:31,670 --> 00:11:33,760
That's really what I thought at first.

168
00:11:35,340 --> 00:11:36,340
But

169
00:11:36,380 --> 00:11:37,740
it's not like that anymore.

170
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:39,530
I'm not good at this,

171
00:11:39,790 --> 00:11:41,330
- but I...
- Don't touch me.

172
00:11:43,260 --> 00:11:44,740
I'm not like you.

173
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:48,890
I should just quit you.

174
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:52,040
This isn't like me at all.

175
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:56,390
If I knew it would hurt this much,

176
00:11:57,950 --> 00:12:00,430
I never would've slept with you.

177
00:12:04,420 --> 00:12:05,720
Fukami...

178
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:11,400
Life isn't a story.

179
00:12:12,460 --> 00:12:14,560
There's no such thing as "the one."

180
00:12:15,810 --> 00:12:19,000
"Happily ever after"

181
00:12:19,025 --> 00:12:19,642
[To Akihiro-chan]

182
00:12:19,690 --> 00:12:21,000
is just a fantasy.

183
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:24,560
That's why I decided

184
00:12:24,900 --> 00:12:27,200
to find comfort with people as lonely as me

185
00:12:27,990 --> 00:12:30,570
and live my life that way.

186
00:12:40,360 --> 00:12:42,080
Of course he's angry.

187
00:12:44,050 --> 00:12:45,610
I trampled on his feelings

188
00:12:45,940 --> 00:12:47,140
and lied to him.

189
00:12:48,060 --> 00:12:49,060
All of this

190
00:12:49,380 --> 00:12:50,770
is my own fault.

191
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:58,470
I don't know how to start a relationship,

192
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:01,290
and I don't know how to end one.

193
00:13:03,860 --> 00:13:06,306
(Next time) Hey, I heard someone
from Tech was in a car accident.

194
00:13:06,330 --> 00:13:08,040
I heard they were brought here.

195
00:13:08,350 --> 00:13:09,310
Are they here?

196
00:13:09,311 --> 00:13:11,220
That person is very important to me.

197
00:13:11,770 --> 00:13:12,650
I like you.

198
00:13:12,651 --> 00:13:15,080
Even if you only look at
me with lust in your eyes...

199
00:13:15,090 --> 00:13:17,570
One day, I'm going to
make him head over heels for me.
